@page "/"
@using MudBlazor

<PageTitle>About Us</PageTitle>

<div style="max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem; font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;">

    <h1 style="font-size: 2.5rem; color: #2c3e50; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        The Salty Pickle At Ballypines Dog Ranch
    </h1>

    <p>
        Located in the Great Bridge area of Chesapeake, Virginia, <strong>The Salty Pickle, LLC</strong> is a private pickleball court rental venue offering a fun and welcoming space for players of all skill levels.
    </p>

    <p>
        Whether you're seeking a competitive match with friends, a private lesson, or an unforgettable event venue, The Salty Pickle has you covered. With a top-quality Flex court and vibrant atmosphere, it's the perfect place to experience the fastest-growing sport in the country.
    </p>

    <p>
        New to the game? We provide beginner lessons to get you started. And if you're planning a social gathering, we're ideal for group play, birthday parties, small corporate events, and team-building activities.
    </p>

    <p>
        We’re open from <strong>7am to 9pm</strong>, with a lit court for nighttime play. Guests can relax in our comfortable seating areas, enjoy the fire pit and cornhole, and take advantage of convenient amenities.
    </p>

    <p>
        What sets us apart is how we blend sport, socializing, and food into one amazing experience. Bring your own catering, invite a food truck, or let your host help arrange a cookout. We even offer an <strong>umpire service</strong> to officiate games and keep score.
    </p>

    <p>
        If you're looking for a truly unique pickleball venue in Chesapeake, look no further — <strong>The Salty Pickle</strong> is the place to be!
    </p>
</div>
<MudCarousel Class="mx-auto my-4"
             Style="width: 100%; max-width: 1000px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;"
             ShowArrows="true"
             ShowBullets="true"
             EnableSwipeGesture="true"
             AutoCycle="true"
             TData="object">

    @foreach (var img in imagePaths)
    {
        <MudCarouselItem>
            <MudImage Src="@img"
                      Alt="Carousel image"
                      Style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;" />
        </MudCarouselItem>
    }
</MudCarousel>

@code {
    private List<string> imagePaths = new()
    {
        "Images/Carousel/court_1.jpg",
        "Images/Carousel/court_2.jpg",
        "Images/Carousel/court_4.jpg",
        "Images/Carousel/garage_2.jpg",
        "Images/Carousel/goats_1.jpg",
        "Images/Carousel/garage_1.jpg",
        "Images/Carousel/garage_3.jpg"
    };
}



